{
  "texts": [
    "The indicator function equates to one if its argument holds true and zero otherwise.",
    "Next, for each gene, we compute its Pearson correlation with GEC, select the top L genes (default 200) and subset X (smoothed) to the identified L genes.",
    "Finally, we mean-aggregate each cell's gene expression",
    "with X ∈ ℝ n c ×L denoting the subsetted, smoothed gene expression matrix X (smoothed).",
    "The CytoTRACE score c is then given by scaling c to the unit interval"
  ]
}